## AI Models
Haiku (claude-haiku-4-5-20251001): image capture, search, assistant preview
Sonnet (dynamic latest, fallback claude-sonnet-4-6): AI assistant, analytics agent

## API Routes
POST /api/capture — Haiku vision → contacts/deals/tasks JSON
POST /api/assistant — Action Agent: Sonnet + 8 tools, user-scoped writes, confirm card preview
POST /api/assistant/preview — Haiku confirm card before write actions
POST /api/analytics-agent — Analytics Agent: Sonnet + 5 read tools, org-scoped
POST /api/sandbox — Haiku routes intent → action or analytics agent, returns agent label
POST /api/sandbox/history — GET conversation list + single conversation
POST /api/search — Haiku intent parsing + Supabase queries
POST /api/nudges — proactive home screen cards
POST /api/tasks — create task
PATCH /api/tasks/[id] — update task
PATCH /api/deals/[id]/stage — kanban drag-drop persist
PATCH /api/analytics-layout — save draggable card layout to org context

## Assistant Tools
Action Agent (8): add_contact, find_contact, add_company, add_deal, add_task, search_crm, get_pipeline_summary, update_deal_stage, update_deal_financials
Analytics Agent (5): get_pipeline_summary, get_deal_velocity, get_stage_conversion, get_revenue_forecast, get_rep_performance

## Database Tables
users, organisations, organisation_members, subscriptions
companies, contacts, deals, deal_contacts, events, tasks
deal_stage_history, conversations

## Schema Notes
contacts: full_name (not first/last), role (not title), next_followup_date
organisation_members: org_id (not organisation_id), role: admin/manager/member
organisations: context jsonb — industry, cycle_days, at_risk_days, team_size, terminology, pain_points[], stage_template, home_priority, analytics_layout
deals stages: lead → qualified → demo → proposal → negotiation → closed_won → closed_lost
deals fields: value, currency, confirmed_revenue, invoice_ref, po_ref, invoice_date, po_date, payment_status (none/invoiced/paid), closed_at, stage_entered_at, expected_close_date, loss_reason
tasks fields: title, status (todo/in_progress/done/cancelled/postponed), done (bool), due_date, priority, postponed_until, deal_id, contact_id, user_id
events: jsonb metadata, every capture and assistant write action logged
DB views: deal_stage_velocity, deal_stage_conversion, rep_quota_attainment
Trigger: handle_stage_change — auto-stamps deal_stage_history on stage change

## Key DB Functions
create_organisation(name, slug) — creates org + admin member + free subscription
get_user_org_id() — returns current user's org
RLS: member=own data, manager=read org, admin=full org
Server components use service role key, client uses anon key

